    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-24T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-24T11:00:00-05:00" n="32"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/1148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-24T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 24, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Regulating decree under the oil law will probably be published in <hi
                        rend="italic">Diario Oficial</hi> today. The date for receiving proposals
                    formerly fixed August 1st will be extended to September 1st; October 15
                    remaining fixed for the other proposals.</p>
                <p>[Paraphrase.] If the regulating decree is published in the form President Olaya
                    said he was accepting yesterday, it will be highly satisfactory. The extension
                    to September 1st was made at the suggestion of Mr. Metzger. [End
                    paraphrase.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
